1/**
2* @author Joseph Ferraro
3*
4* Utility class for calculating rollups on Lookup relationships
5*/
6
7public class GLBL_RollupSummaryUtility {
8     
9    //the following class will be used to house the field names
10    //and desired operations
11    public class fieldDefinition {
12        public String operation {get;set;}
13        public String childField {get;set;}
14        public String parentField {get;set;}
15         
16        public fieldDefinition (String o, String c, String p) {
17            operation = o;
18            childField = c;
19            parentField = p;
20        }
21    }
22     
23    public static void rollUpTrigger(list<fieldDefinition> fieldDefinitions,
24    list<sObject> records, String childObject, String childParentLookupField, 
25    String parentObject, String queryFilter) {
26         
27        //Limit the size of list by using Sets which do not contain duplicate
28        //elements prevents hitting governor limits
29        set<Id> parentIds = new set<Id>();
30         
31        for(sObject s : records) {
32            parentIds.add((Id)s.get(childParentLookupField));
33        }
34         
35        //populate query text strings to be used in child aggregrator and 
36        //parent value assignment
37        String fieldsToAggregate = '';
38        String parentFields = '';
39         
40        for(fieldDefinition d : fieldDefinitions) {
41            fieldsToAggregate += d.operation + '(' + d.childField + ') ' + 
42            ', ';
43            parentFields += d.parentField + ', ';
44        }
45         
46        //Using dynamic SOQL with aggergate results to populate parentValueMap
47        String aggregateQuery = 'Select ' + fieldsToAggregate + 
48        childParentLookupField + ' from ' + childObject + ' where  ' + 
49        childParentLookupField + ' IN :parentIds ' + queryFilter + ' ' +
50        ' group by ' + childParentLookupField;
51        
52        system.debug('aggregate query >>> '+aggregateQuery);
53 
54        //Map will contain one parent record Id per one aggregate object
55        map<Id, AggregateResult> parentValueMap = 
56        new map <Id, AggregateResult>();
57         
58        for(AggregateResult q : Database.query(aggregateQuery)){
59            parentValueMap.put((Id)q.get(childParentLookupField), q);
60        }
61
62        system.debug('parentValueMap >>> '+parentValueMap);
63
64        //list of parent object records to update
65        list<sObject> parentsToUpdate = new list<sObject>();
66         
67        String parentQuery = 'select ' + parentFields + ' Id ' +
68         ' from ' + parentObject + ' where Id IN :parentIds';
69        
70        system.debug('parent query >>> '+parentQuery);
71
72        //for each affected parent object, retrieve aggregate results and 
73        //for each field definition add aggregate value to parent field
74        for(sObject s : Database.query(parentQuery)) {
75             
76            Integer row = 0; //row counter reset for every parent record
77            for(fieldDefinition d : fieldDefinitions) {
78                String field = 'expr' + row.format();
79                AggregateResult r = parentValueMap.get(s.Id);
80                //r will be null if no records exist 
81                //(e.g. last record deleted)
82                if(r != null) { 
83                    Decimal value = ((Decimal)r.get(field) == null ) ? 0 : 
84                        (Decimal)r.get(field);
85                    s.put(d.parentField, value);
86                } else {
87                    s.put(d.parentField, 0);
88                }
89                row += 1; //plus 1 for every field definition after first
90            }
91            parentsToUpdate.add(s);
92        }
93         
94        //if parent records exist, perform update of all parent records 
95        //with a single DML statement
96        if(parentsToUpdate.Size() > 0) {
97            update parentsToUpdate;
98        }
99         
100    }
101 
102}

27/**
28 * Serializes and Deserializes SObject records and related child and referenced records using the Apex JSON support
29 *
30 *   See https://github.com/afawcett/apex-sobjectdataloader for known issues, restrictions and TODO's
31 *
32 **/
33public with sharing class GLBL_SobjectDataLoader 
34{
35    /**
36     * Configuration uses a Fluent method design (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluent_interface), 
37     **/
38    public class SerializeConfig
39    {
40        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followRelationships;
41        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followChildRelationships;
42        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followMasterRelationships;
43        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> omitFields;
44        
45        public SerializeConfig()
46        {    
47            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
48            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
49            followMasterRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
50            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();             
51        }
52        
53        /**
54         * Provide a field that represents the lookup relationship the serializer should follow
55         **/
56        public SerializeConfig follow(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
57        {
58            followRelationships.add(relationshipField);
59            return this;
60        }
61
62        /**
63         * Provide a field that represents the lookup relationship the serializer should follow
64         **/
65        public SerializeConfig followMaster(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
66        {
67            followMasterRelationships.add(relationshipField);
68            return this;
69        }
70        
71        /**
72         * Provide a field that represents a parent child relationship the serializer should follow
73         **/
74        public SerializeConfig followChild(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
75        {
76            followChildRelationships.add(relationshipField);
77            return this;
78        }
79        
80        /**
81         * Provide a field that the serializer should omit from the serialized output
82         **/
83        public SerializeConfig omit(Schema.SObjectField omitField)
84        {
85            omitFields.add(omitField);
86            if(followRelationships.contains(omitField))
87                followRelationships.remove(omitField);
88            if(followChildRelationships.contains(omitField))
89                followChildRelationships.remove(omitField);
90            return this;
91        }
92        
93        /** 
94         * Automatically configure (removes all previous configuration)
95         *  Skip known system lookup and child relationships but include the rest (direct children only) upto certain depth, 
96         *  Caller can always add or omit specific via follow or omit methods
97         **/
98        public SerializeConfig auto(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType)
99        {
100            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
101            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
102            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
103            Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched = new Set<Schema.SObjectType>();
104            searchRelationships(sObjectType, 0, 0, true, searched);    
105            return this;    
106        }
107        
108        /**
109         * Seek out recursively relationships
110         **/
111        private void searchRelationships(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, Boolean searchChildren, Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched)
112        {        
113            // Stop infinite recursion    
114            if(searched.contains(sObjectType) || lookupDepth > 2 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
115                return;
116            searched.add(sObjectType);
117            Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDescribe = sObjectType.getDescribe();
118                        
119            // Following children? (only set for descendents of the top level object)
120            if(searchChildren)
121            {
122                List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDescribe.getChildRelationships();
123                for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
124                {
125                    // Determine which child relationships to automatically follow
126                    String childRelationshipName = childRelationship.getRelationshipName();
127                    if(childRelationshipName==null || 
128                       childRelationshipWhitelist.contains(childRelationshipName)) // Skip relationships without names and those whitelisted
129                        continue;
130                    if(childRelationshipName.endsWith('Histories')) // Skip relationships ending in Histories (TODO: consider a RegEx approach?)
131                        continue;
132                    if(!childRelationship.isCascadeDelete()) // Skip relationships for none owned records (aka only follow master-detail relationships)
133                        continue;
134                    followChild(childRelationship.getField()).
135                        searchRelationships(childRelationship.getChildSObject(), lookupDepth, childDepth+1, true, searched);
136                }
137            }
138                            
139            // Follow lookup relationships to long as they have not previously been added as child references and are not whitelisted
140            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDescribe.fields.getMap();
141            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
142                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
143                    if(!followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField) && !relationshipWhitelist.contains(sObjectField.getDescribe().getName()))
144                        follow(sObjectField).
145                            searchRelationships(sObjectField.getDescribe().getReferenceTo()[0], lookupDepth+1, childDepth, false, searched);
146        }
147
148        // Standard fields that are not included when using the auto config
149        private Set<String> relationshipWhitelist = 
150            new Set<String>
151                { 'OwnerId',
152                  'CreatedById',
153                  'LastModifiedById',
154                  'RecordTypeId',
155                  'PersonContactId'
156                };
157                
158        // Standard child relationships that are not included when using the auto config
159        private Set<String> childRelationshipWhitelist = 
160            new Set<String> 
161                { 'Shares', 
162                  'ProcessInstances', 
163                  'ProcessSteps', 
164                  'Tasks', 
165                  'ActivityHistories', 
166                  'Attachments', 
167                  'FeedSubscriptionsForEntity', 
168                  'Events', 
169                  'Notes', 
170                  'NotesAndAttachments', 
171                  'OpenActivities', 
172                  'Histories', 
173                  'Feeds',
174                  'PersonEmailStatuses',
175                  'OpenActivities',
176                  'PersonOpenActivities'};    
177    }
178

180    /**
181     * Serialize the given records using the default configuration (see SerializeConfig.auto)
182     **/
183    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids)
184    {
185        // Serialize based on no prior knowledge of the objects
186        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
187            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
188        return serialize(ids, new SerializeConfig().auto(new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType()));
189    }
190    
191    /**
192     * Serialize the given records using the given configuration
193     **/
194    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids, SerializeConfig strategy)
195    {            
196        // Validate parameters
197        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
198            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
199            
200        // Container to bundle record sets into 
201        RecordsBundle recordsToBundle = new RecordsBundle();
202        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles = new List<RecordSetBundle>();        
203        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType = new Map<String, RecordSetBundle>();
204        
205        // Begin recursive serialize from given records through to related records
206        Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType();
207        serialize(ids, sObjectType, null, strategy, 0, 0, recordsToBundle);
208                
209        // Serialise the records bundle container        
210        return JSON.serialize(recordsToBundle);                 
211    }
212
213    /**
214     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle
215     **/
216    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON)
217    {
218        return deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, null);
219    }
220        
221    /**
222     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle utilising the given callback
223     **/
224    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON, IDeserializeCallback callback)
225    {
226        // Desearialise the records bundle
227        RecordsBundle recordsBundle = (RecordsBundle) 
228            JSON.deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, GLBL_SobjectDataLoader.RecordsBundle.class);
229        
230        // Map to track original ID's against the new SObject record instances being inserted
231        Map<Id, SObject> recordsByOriginalId = new Map<Id, SObject>();
232        
233        // Record set bundles are already ordered in dependency order due to serialisation approach
234        Map<String, Schema.SObjectType> sObjectsByType = Schema.getGlobalDescribe();
235        for(RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle : recordsBundle.recordSetBundles)
236        {
237            // Determine lookup / relationship fields to update prior to inserting these records
238            Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = sObjectsByType.get(recordSetBundle.ObjectType);
239            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectType.getDescribe().fields.getMap();
240            List<Schema.SObjectField> relationshipsFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>();
241            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
242                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
243                    relationshipsFields.add(sObjectField);
244                                    
245            // Prepare records for insert
246            List<SObject> recordsToInsert = new List<SObject>();
247            List<UnresolvedReferences> unresolvedReferencesByRecord = new List<UnresolvedReferences>(); 
248            for(SObject orignalRecord : recordSetBundle.Records)
249            {
250                // Clone the deserialised SObject to remove the original Id prior to inserting it
251                SObject newRecord = orignalRecord.clone();
252                recordsToInsert.add(newRecord);
253                // Map the new cloned record to its old Id (once inserted this can be used to obtain the new id)
254                recordsByOriginalId.put(orignalRecord.Id, newRecord);
255                // Update foreign key references / lookups / master-detail relationships
256                if(relationshipsFields.size()>0)
257                {
258                    Set<Schema.SObjectField> unresolvedFieldReferences = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
259                    for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : relationshipsFields)
260                    {                            
261                        // Obtained original related record Id and search map over new records by old Ids
262                        Id oldRelatedRecordId = (Id) orignalRecord.get(sObjectField);
263                        SObject newRelatedRecord = recordsByOriginalId.get(oldRelatedRecordId);
264                        if(newRelatedRecord!=null)
265                            newRecord.put(sObjectField, newRelatedRecord.Id);
266                        else
267                            unresolvedFieldReferences.add(sObjectField);
268                    }
269                    // Retain a list of records with unresolved references
270                    if(unresolvedFieldReferences.size()>0)
271                    {
272                        UnresolvedReferences unresolvedReferences = new UnresolvedReferences();
273                        unresolvedReferences.Record = newRecord;
274                        unresolvedReferences.References = unresolvedFieldReferences;
275                        unresolvedReferencesByRecord.add(unresolvedReferences);
276                    }    
277                }
278            }            
279            
280            // Let the caller attempt to resolve any references the above could not
281            if(callback!=null && unresolvedReferencesByRecord.size()>0)
282                callback.unresolvedReferences(sObjectType, unresolvedReferencesByRecord);
283            
284            if(callback!=null)
285                callback.cloneMapHandler(recordsByOriginalId);
286
287            // Insert cloned deserialised records
288            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToInsert;
289            insert recordSetBundle.Records;
290        }
291        
292        // Return Id list from the first bundle set
293        return new Map<Id, SObject>(recordsBundle.recordSetBundles[0].Records).keySet();
294    }
295            
296    private static void serialize(Set<ID> ids, Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Schema.SObjectField queryByIdField, SerializeConfig config, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, RecordsBundle recordsToBundle)
297    {        
298        // Config?
299        if(config==null)
300            throw new SerializerException('Must pass a valid SerializeConfig instance.');
301        // Stop infinite recursion
302        if(lookupDepth > 3 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
303            return;
304            
305        // Describe object and determine fields to serialize
306        Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDesc = sObjectType.getDescribe();
307        Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDesc.fields.getMap();
308        List<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFieldsToSerialize = listFieldsToSerialize(sObjectFields, config);
309        
310        // Query records to serialize
311        String fieldList = null;
312        for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFieldsToSerialize)
313            fieldList = fieldList == null ? sObjectField.getDescribe().getName() : fieldList + ',' + sObjectField.getDescribe().getName();
314        String query = String.format('select {0} from {1} where {2} in :ids order by {2}', 
315            new List<String> { fieldList, sObjectDesc.getName(), queryByIdField == null ? 'id' : queryByIdField.getDescribe().getName(), 'Name' });
316        Map<Id, SObject> recordsToSerializeById = new Map<Id, SObject>(Database.query(query));
317        if(recordsToSerializeById.size()==0)
318            return;
319
320        // Any lookup relationships to folow?
321        Set<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFollowRelationships = config.followRelationships.clone();
322        sObjectFollowRelationships.retainAll(sObjectFields.values());
323        if(sObjectFollowRelationships.size()>0)
324        {                
325            // Build list of ID's for each related record
326            Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>> relationshipsByField = new Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>>(); 
327            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFollowRelationships)
328                relationShipsByField.put(sObjectField.getDescribe(), new Set<Id>() );            
329            for(SObject recordToSerialize : recordsToSerializeById.values())
330            {
331                for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
332                {
333                    Id relatedId = (Id) recordToSerialize.get(relationshipField.getSObjectField());
334                    if(relatedId!=null)
335                        relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField).add(relatedId);
336                }
337            }
338            // Serialise related records
339            for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
340            {
341                Set<Id> relatedRecordIds = relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField);
342                if(relatedRecordIds.size()>0)
343                    serialize(relatedRecordIds, relationshipField.getReferenceTo()[0], null, config, lookupDepth+1, childDepth, recordsToBundle);                    
344            }
345        }
346                    
347        // Add records to applicable record set bundle
348        RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle = recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.get(sObjectDesc.getName());
349        if(recordSetBundle!=null)
350        {
351            recordSetBundle.Records.addAll(recordsToSerializeById.values());
352        }
353        else if(recordSetBundle==null)
354        {
355            recordSetBundle = new RecordSetBundle();
356            recordSetBundle.ObjectType = sObjectDesc.getName();
357            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToSerializeById.values();
358            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles.add(recordSetBundle);
359            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.put(recordSetBundle.ObjectType, recordSetBundle);
360        }
361                
362        // Any child relationships to follow?
363        List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDesc.getChildRelationships();
364        for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
365        { 
366            // Is this a child relationship we have been asked to follow?
367            Schema.SObjectType childSObjectType = childRelationship.getChildSObject();
368            if(config.followChildRelationships.contains(childRelationship.getField()))
369                serialize(recordsToSerializeById.keySet(), childSObjectType, childRelationship.getField(), config, lookupDepth, childDepth+1, recordsToBundle);
370        }
371    }
372    
373    private static List<Schema.SObjectField> listFieldsToSerialize(Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields, SerializeConfig config)
374    {
375        // Filter fields to serialise
376        List<Schema.SObjectField> serializeFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
377        List<String> fieldNames = new List<String>(sObjectFields.keySet());
378        fieldNames.sort();
379        for(String fieldName : fieldNames)
380        {
381            // Skip fields indicated in config
382            Schema.SObjectField sObjectField = sObjectFields.get(fieldName);
383            if(config.omitFields!=null && config.omitFields.contains(sObjectField))
384                continue;
385            // Skip read only fields, such as auto numbers and formula fields
386            Schema.DescribeFieldResult sObjectFieldDescribe = sObjectField.getDescribe();
387            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.isAutoNumber() ||
388               sObjectFieldDescribe.isCalculated())
389               continue;    
390            // Skip lookup fields not in either of the follow lists
391            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference)
392                if(!(config.followRelationships.contains(sObjectField) ||
393                     config.followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField) ||
394                     config.followMasterRelationships.contains(sObjectField)))
395                   continue;
396            // Serialize this field..                        
397            serializeFields.add(sObjectField);
398        }            
399        return serializeFields;    
400    }
401    
402    /** 
403     * General exception class
404     **/
405    public class SerializerException extends Exception
406    {
407        
408    }

418        void unresolvedReferences(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, List<UnresolvedReferences> unresolvedReferences);
419        void cloneMapHAndler(Map<Id, SObject> cloneMap);
420    }

424     **/
425    public class UnresolvedReferences
426    {

429    }

GLBL_TriggerHandler.cls

(89% covered)

Show Coverage
1/**
2 * @author Joseph Ferraro
3 *
4 * Generic handler for Trigger actions
5 */
6
7public class GLBL_TriggerHandler 
8{
9    /**
10     *   Enum representing each of before/after CRUD events on Sobjects
11     */
12    public enum Evt 
13    {
14        afterdelete, afterinsert, afterundelete,
15        afterupdate, beforedelete, beforeinsert, beforeupdate   
16    }
17
18    /*
19     *   Simplistic handler to implement on any of the event. It doesn't require or enforces any pattern except the
20     *   method name to be "handle()".
21     */
22    public interface HandlerInterface
23    {
24        void handle();          
25    } 
26
27    // Internal mapping of handlers
28    map<String, list<HandlerInterface>> eventHandlerMapping = new map<String, list<HandlerInterface>>();
29
30    /**
31     *   Core API to bind handlers with events
32     */
33    public GLBL_TriggerHandler bind(Evt event, HandlerInterface eh)
34    {
35        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(event.name());
36        if (handlers == null) 
37        {
38            handlers = new list<HandlerInterface>();
39            eventHandlerMapping.put(event.name(), handlers);
40        }
41        handlers.add(eh);
42        return this;
43    }
44
45    /**
46     *   Invokes correct handlers as per the context of trigger and available registered handlers
47     */
48    public void manage()
49    {
50        Evt ev = null;
51        if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isBefore)
52        {
53            ev = Evt.beforeinsert;
54        }
55        else if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isAfter)
56        {
57            ev = Evt.afterinsert;
58        }
59        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isBefore)
60        {
61            ev = Evt.beforeupdate;
62        }
63        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isAfter)
64        {
65            ev = Evt.afterupdate;
66        }
67        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isBefore)
68        {
69            ev = Evt.beforedelete;
70        }
71        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isAfter)
72        {
73            ev = Evt.afterdelete;
74        }
75        else if(trigger.isundelete)
76        {
77            ev = Evt.afterundelete;             
78        }
79        
80        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(ev.name());
81        
82        if (handlers != null && ! handlers.isEmpty()) 
83        {
84            for (HandlerInterface h : handlers) 
85            {
86                h.handle();
87            }
88        }
89    }
90}

17    void execute(List<SObject> sobjects) {
18        List<Sobject> participantsToRollup;
19        
20        if (this.triggeredSobjectAPIName == null)
21            triggeredSobjectAPIName = MERC_Util.getSobjectAPIName(sobjects.get(0));

23        if (triggeredSobjectAPIName == 'Meeting_MERC__c') {

25            Set<Id> meetingIdsToProcess = new Set<Id>();
26            for (Meeting_MERC__c m : meetings) {
27                if (
28                    Trigger.oldMap.get(m.Id).get('Meeting_Status_MERC__c') != m.Meeting_Status_MERC__c ||
29                    Trigger.oldMap.get(m.Id).get('End_Date_of_Event_MERC__c') != m.End_Date_of_Event_MERC__c
30                ) {
31                    meetingIdsToProcess.add(m.Id);
32                }
33            }
34            participantsToRollup = [SELECT ID, Account_MERC__c, Meeting_MERC__c FROM Meeting_Participant_MERC__c WHERE 
35                                        Meeting_MERC__c in :meetingIdsToProcess];
36        } else if (triggeredSobjectAPIName == 'Meeting_Participant_MERC__c') {
37            participantsToRollup = sobjects;
38        }
39

41            GLBL_Rollup.RollupService.triggerHandler(participantsToRollup);
42    }

79    public static String generateRandomString(Integer count) {
80        String chars = '0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXTZabcdefghiklmnopqrstuvwxyz';
81        String hash = '';
82        for (integer i = 0; i < count; i++) {
83            Integer rnum = Math.floor(Math.random() * chars.length()).intValue();
84            hash += chars.substring(rnum,rnum+1);
85        }
86        return hash;
87    }

364        searchAddress.City_GLBL__c = searchAddress.City_GLBL__c != null ? (searchAddress.City_GLBL__c.length() > 0 ? String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c.trim()) : '') : '';
365        searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c = searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c != null ? (searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c.length() > 0 ? String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c.trim()) : '') : '';
366        
367        searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
368        
369        //Make sure something is filled out
370        didTryCreate = false;
371        if (String.isBlank(searchAccount.FirstName) && String.isBlank(searchAccount.LastName) && String.isBlank(searchAccount.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAccount.Phone) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c)) {
372            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.Search_Term_Required_MVN));
373            return null;
374        }

377        if (!String.isBlank(searchAccount.Phone)) {
378            searchResults = buildPhoneSearchResults();
379        } else if (String.isBlank(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c)) {
380            searchResults = buildAccountSearchResults();
381        } else {
382            searchResults = buildAddressSearchResults();
383        }
384
385        if(searchResults == null) {
386            searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
387            return null;
388        }
389
390        if (searchResults.size() >= SEARCHLIMIT) {
391            searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
392            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.Too_Many_Results_MVN));
393        } else if (searchResults.size() == 0 ) {
394            searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
395            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.No_Search_Results_MVN));
396        }
397

399        didSearch = true;
400        showNewButton = true;
401        return null;

530    public String buildSOSLString(){
531        //Put together final query and error check it
532        String qString = 'FIND {';
533        String findString = '';
534
535        //Cannot search for phone numbers with punctuation
536        findString = searchAccount.Phone.replaceAll('[^0-9]', '');
537        if (findString.length() < 2) {
538            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.SOSL_Phone_Search_Min_Char_MVN + ' ' + findString));
539            return null;
540        }
541
542        qString += findString + '} IN PHONE FIELDS RETURNING ';
543        qString += ' Address_GLBL__c (' + ADDRESSFIELDS;
544        qString += buildAddressWhereClause();
545        qString += ADDRESSORDERBY;
546        qString += '), ';
547        qString += ' Account (' + ACCOUNTFIELDS;
548        qString += buildAccountWhereClause();
549        qString += ACCOUNTORDERBY;
550        qString += ') ';
551
552        return qString;
553    }
554
555    public String buildAccountWhereClause() {
556        String acctString = '';
557        acctString +=' WHERE IsDeleted = false ';
558
559        Map<String,String> fieldMap = new Map<String,String>();
560        fieldMap.put('LastName like',searchAccount.LastName);
561        fieldMap.put('FirstName like',searchAccount.FirstName);
562        fieldMap.put('Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c like',searchAccount.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c);
563
564        for(String field : fieldMap.keySet()) {
565            String sTerm = fieldMap.get(field);
566            if(sTerm != null && !String.isBlank(sTerm)){
567                acctString += ' AND (' + field + ' \'' + sTerm.replaceAll('\\*', '%') + '\')';
568            }
569        }
570
571        if(recordTypeText == 'All') {
572            acctString += ' AND (RecordTypeId in :validRecordTypeIds)';
573        } else {
574            acctString += ' AND (RecordTypeId = \'' + recordTypeText + '\')';
575        }
576
577        return acctString;
578    }
579
580    public String buildAddressWhereClause() {
581        String addrString = ' WHERE IsDeleted = false ';
582
583        Map<String,String> fieldMap = new Map<String,String>();
584        fieldMap.put('City_GLBL__c like',searchAddress.City_GLBL__c);
585        fieldMap.put('St_Cd_GLBL__c =',searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c);
586        fieldMap.put('Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c like',searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c);
587        fieldMap.put('Adrs_Cntry_Cd_GLBL__c =',searchAddress.Adrs_Cntry_Cd_GLBL__c);
588        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.LastName like',searchAccount.LastName);
589        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.FirstName like',searchAccount.FirstName);
590        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c like',searchAccount.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c);
591
592        for(String field : fieldMap.keySet()) {
593            String sTerm = fieldMap.get(field);
594            if(sTerm != null && !String.isBlank(sTerm)){
595                addrString += ' AND (' + field + ' \'' + sTerm.replaceAll('\\*', '%') + '\')';
596            }
597        }
598
599        if(recordTypeText == 'All') {
600            addrString += ' AND (Account_GLBL__r.RecordTypeId in :validRecordTypeIds)';
601        } else {
602            addrString += ' AND (Account_GLBL__r.RecordTypeId = \'' + recordTypeText + '\')';
603        }
604
605        return addrString;
606    }
